Stacked Denoising Autoencoders - Fraud Detection¶

Brian Chen¶

CISC 874¶

Recap: SDAE¶

  • Autoencoders are structured like MLPs
    • Symmetrical structure (input size = output size)
    • Minimize reconstruction loss
  • Denoising tries to reconstruct clean output from perturbed input
    • Can improve generalization
  • Stacking trains multiple AEs in sequence
    • Enables gradual training of increasingly abstract representations

Correlation Matrix¶

  • 43 features total (excluding vwretd-t1) + labels

Preprocessing¶

  • Scaled continuous columns using z-scores
    • Min-max scaling too sensitive to outliers
  • Imputed missing values
    • Mode/median/mean values per column
    • SVD-imputation (thanks #y-dataset!)
